author: @sentdex
text: Daniel pointed out: the issue with online/idle/offline was actually the if elif else was actually an if if else, thus double-counting online in the sense that "idle" also includes online people.  Surprised no one else noticed after 2500 views, but oops :)

author: @tkon99
text: Anyone with a tag (like moderator) does not count as online in the discord client, they do count as online in the api though (because they are). Discord just separates users based on their tags. Hence the different numbers.
